# Recenter has no backend and no required environment variables today.
# All data lives on-device via AsyncStorage; there are no API keys, no
# database URL, and no auth secrets to configure.
#
# This file exists so the pattern is in place before Recenter needs its
# first real environment variable — add new vars here as they're
# introduced, with a comment explaining what each one is for. Expo only
# exposes variables prefixed with EXPO_PUBLIC_ to app code; anything
# without that prefix stays server/build-only.
#
# Example of the pattern to follow when a real variable is added:
# EXPO_PUBLIC_EXAMPLE_FLAG=false
